snowberry
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a name applied to a number of plants, including mingimingi (prickly heath).  See also Taupo snowberry, rock snowberry, weka berry
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Kerry Carman writes (Sept. 2000): <i>Gaultheria antipoda</i> is the Bush Snowberry; fruits are 15 mm and may be white, pink, red or purple. Confusing the issue are two other candidates, also commonly called snowberries. (a). <i>Pernettya</i> is also an edible Snowberry, sometimes white, sometimes red. Like <i>Gaultheria</i> it is of the <i>Ericaceae</i> with which it bydrisies freely in the wild. (b). <i>Leucopogon (Epacridaceae)</i> is another edible native Snowberry from the region. It ranges from white through pinks and red to purple.
