Author: CROWE
Vol / Page: 53
Edition:
Quote: Snowberry <i>Gaultheria antipoda</i> Tawiniwini; bush snowberry <i>Gaultheria depressa</i> Mountain snowberry... Both shrubs are rather similar except that bush snowberry grows up to about 1.5 metres and has leaves 80-16mm long, while mountain snowberry is a low spreading plant seldom more than 10 cm high, with smaller leaves 4-8 mm long. <i>Ibid.</i> 54 In 1864, Barrington.. was grateful at one point for the sustenance these fruits provided: 'I was so weak that I thought I must give in, but I ate plenty of the little snowberries which grow under the snow. They helped us a good deal.'
