Vol / Page: 211
Edition:
Quote: Gaultheria. Ericaceae. A genus of 120 species of shrubby plants found mainly in the Americas. There are about 10 New Zealand species, of which all but 1 are endemic. Their common name is snowberry because they bear white to pinkish red fruit.
