Quote: The pink, red or white berries of this shrub were gathered in the past by men of the village when larger, more tasty berries were unobtainable. Snowberries are a favourite food of the weka bird, they were also sought by the early sheep musterers and prospectors of Otago in the high country when emergency rations were needed.
