Date: 0/0/1990
Source: Native Edible Plants of NZ
Author: CROWE
Vol / Page: 54
Edition:
Quote: Richards describes the fruit of the creeping mountain snowberry as 'edible and rather tasteless.' Earlier travellers, who had perhaps worked up a better appetite, have kinder words for them; J.T. Thomson, while exploring South Otago in 1857, seemed to appreciate the New Zealand strawberry, as he called it, and likens it to the rose apple of India.
Notes: 1st ed. 1981

